7 Chapter 6.8. Relocation of Casino Operations
8 Sec. 1. For purposes of this chapter, "Ohio County license"
9 means an owner's license for a riverboat operated from Ohio
10 County.
11 Sec. 2. For purposes of this chapter, "permit holder" has the
12 meaning set forth in IC 4-31-2.1-27.
13 Sec. 3. The commission may authorize in the manner required
14 by this chapter the relocation of the Ohio County license to an
15 inland casino in Allen County, DeKalb County, Steuben County, or
16 Wayne County.
17 Sec. 4. (a) A licensed owner or permit holder may apply to own
18 and operate the Ohio County license by submitting the following
19 to the commission not later than December 1, 2026:
20 (1) A written application that contains the following
21 information:
22 (A) The county in which the applicant is proposing to
23 operate an inland casino. For purposes of this clause, the
24 application must select Allen County, DeKalb County,
25 Steuben County, or Wayne County.
26 (B) Documented and verifiable information describing the
27 following:
28 (i) The proposed site of the inland casino.
29 (ii) Evidence of site control or real estate options.
30 (iii) Conceptual plans for casino and nongaming
31 facilities.
32 (iv) Estimated construction and total development costs.
33 (v) A phased investment and construction timeline.
34 (vi) Market and feasibility information.
35 (vii) The financial capacity of the applicant.
36 (C) The applicant's commitment and plan to invest at least
37 five hundred million dollars ($500,000,000) for the
38 development of a casino and nongaming amenities onsite
39 in the county selected under clause (A) in the following
40 manner:
41 (i) At least sixty percent (60%) of the amount invested in
42 the initial phase of development.
