10 SECTION 7. IC 4-33-12-1.5, AS AMENDED BY P.L.293-2019,
11 SECTION 24, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
12 UPON PASSAGE]: Sec. 1.5. (a) A supplemental wagering tax on the
13 wagering occurring each day at a riverboat is imposed upon the
14 licensed owner operating the riverboat.
15 (b) Except as provided in subsection (d), subsections (d) and (e),
16 and subject to subsection (c), the amount of supplemental wagering tax
17 imposed for a particular day is determined by multiplying the
18 riverboat's adjusted gross receipts for that day by the quotient of:
19 (1) the total riverboat admissions tax that the riverboat's licensed
20 owner paid beginning July 1, 2016, and ending June 30, 2017;
21 divided by
22 (2) the riverboat's adjusted gross receipts beginning July 1, 2016,
23 and ending June 30, 2017.
24 (c) The quotient used under subsection (b) to determine the
25 supplemental wagering tax liability of a licensed owner subject to
26 subsection (b) may not exceed the following when expressed as a
27 percentage:
28 (1) Four percent (4%) before July 1, 2019.
29 (2) Three and five-tenths percent (3.5%) after June 30, 2019.
30 (d) The supplemental wagering tax liability of a licensed owner
31 operating an inland casino in Vigo County is equal to two and
32 nine-tenths percent (2.9%) of the riverboat's adjusted gross receipts for
33 the day.
34 (e) The supplemental wagering tax liability of a licensed owner
35 operating an inland casino in Allen County, DeKalb County,
36 Steuben County, or Wayne County under IC 4-33-6.8 is equal to
37 three and five-tenths percent (3.5%) of the riverboat's adjusted
38 gross receipts for the day.
